INSTALL
............

Once you place the directory in your prefereable location, do the following:

arche.sh --install


Requierements:
-------------
p7zip
bedtools >= 2.27.0
barrnap
Prodigal
GeneMarkS-2
Infernal 1.1.4 (I don't recommend apt installing)
tRNAscan-SE (I don't recommend apt installing)
blastp
DIAMOND
FASTA36
hmmer
faSomeRecords


Install 'p7zip', 'blastp', 'diamond', 'barrnap', 'bedtools', 'Prodigal' and 'hmmer'
----------------------------------------------------------------
Some of them come by default in the latest linux distributions. Check if they're already installed in your computer. If not:

sudo apt-get install p7zip-full

sudo apt-get install diamond-aligner

sudo apt-get install ncbi-blast+

sudo apt-get install hmmer

sudo apt-get install barrnap

sudo apt-get install prodigal

sudo apt-get install bedtools [version must be >= 2.27.0]

-----In case of failure, install manually: -----

For << BLAST >> binaries, go to https://ftp.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/blast/executables/blast+/LATEST/ and download the latest version.

cd
tar xvfz ncbi-blast-[VERSION]+-x64-linux.tar.gz
sudo mv ncbi-blast-[VERSION]+ /opt/
sudo cp -s /opt/ncbi-blast-[VERSION]+/bin/* /usr/bin/

<< DIAMOND >> binaries:

cd
git clone 'https://github.com/bbuchfink/diamond.git'
cd diamond/
mkdir bin
cd bin
cmake ..
make install
cd
sudo mv diamond /opt/
sudo cp -s /opt/diamond/bin/diamond /usr/bin/

<< hmmer >>
Download it from http://hmmer.org/download.html

cd
tar xvfz hmmer-3.3.tar.gz
cd hmmer-3.3/
./configure
make
sudo make install

<< bedtools >>
Download from https://github.com/arq5x/bedtools2/releases

cd
tar xvfz bedtools-2.30.0.tar.gz
cd bedtools2/
make
cd
sudo mv bedtools2/ /opt/
sudo cp -s /opt/bedtools2/bin/* /usr/bin/

<< Prodigal >>

git clone https://github.com/hyattpd/Prodigal.git
cd Prodigal/
sudo make install
cd
sudo mv Prodigal/ /opt/

<< barrnap >>

cd
git clone https://github.com/tseemann/barrnap.git
sudo cp barrnap/bin/barrnap /usr/bin/



Install ssearch36 and map_db (FASTA36 package)
-------------------------------------------
cd
git clone https://github.com/wrpearson/fasta36.git
cd fasta36/src/
make -f ../make/Makefile.linux_sse2 all
cd
sudo mv fasta36/ /opt/
sudo cp -s /opt/fasta36/bin/{ssearch36,map_db} /usr/bin/


Install faSomeRecords
-------------------
Download it from http://hgdownload.cse.ucsc.edu/admin/exe/linux.x86_64/ [arche works fine with this version of faSomeRecords, I can't be sure about other]

sudo cp faSomeRecords /usr/bin/

Install infernal
------------

tar xvfz infernal-1.1.4.tar.gz
cd infernal-1.1.4/
./configure
make
sudo make install
sudo mv infernal-1.1.4 /opt/

Install tRNAscan-SE
------------------
Download it from http://lowelab.ucsc.edu/tRNAscan-SE/

cd
tar xvfz trnascan-se-2.0.9.tar.gz
cd tRNAscan-SE-2.0
make
sudo make install
sudo mv tRNAscan-SE-2.0/ /opt/

Install GeneMarkS-2
------------------
Download GeneMarkS-2 and key from http://exon.gatech.edu/GeneMark/license_download.cgi

gunzip gm_key_64.gz
tar xvfz gms2_linux_64.tar.gz
cp gm_key_64 ~/.gmhmmp2_key
sudo mv gms2_linux_64 /opt/
cp -s /opt/gms2_linux_64/{biogem,compp,gmhmmp2,gms2.pl} /usr/bin/

USAGE
.........

BlastP annotation of a bacterial genome, using 20 threads and enabling 40 GB of memory:

arche.sh -n ecoli -t 20 -r 40 e_coli.fna

SSEARCH annotation of an archaeal genome, using 1 thread and enabling 2 GB of memory:

arche.sh -n halorubrum -a ssearch -k achaea halorubrum_sp_DM2.fa

DIAMOND annotation of a metagenome

arche.sh -n seawater_meatgenome -k meta seawater_metagenome.fna














